{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JgREwhSRdVuUCvmCARs9Rj","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 5.1: Flow Execution — Sequential Steps\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want the engine to execute flow steps sequentially,\n9\tso that tasks run in defined order with state checkpointed after each task.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a `workflow-engine.ts` module at `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`\n14\t   **When** inspected\n15\t   **Then** it exports an `executeWorkflow(config: EngineConfig): Promise<EngineResult>` function that orchestrates sequential flow execution\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** a resolved workflow with `flow: [implement, verify]` where `implement` has `scope: per-story` and `verify` has `scope: per-run`\n19\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called\n20\t   **Then** the `implement` task runs once for each story/issue in the sprint before the `verify` task runs\n21\t   **And** `verify` runs exactly once after all per-story tasks complete\n22\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n23\t\n24\t3. **Given** a sprint-status.yaml with stories `[\"3-1-foo\", \"3-2-bar\"]` both in backlog/ready-for-dev status\n25\t   **When** the engine executes a `per-story` task\n26\t   **Then** it dispatches the agent once for story `3-1-foo` and once for story `3-2-bar`, in order\n27\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t4. **Given** the engine completes a task dispatch for a story\n30\t   **When** the dispatch returns a `DispatchResult`\n31\t   **Then** `writeWorkflowState()` is called with an updated state containing the new `TaskCheckpoint` (task_name, story_key, completed_at, session_id)\n32\t   **And** state is written to disk before the next task begins\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** sprint-status.yaml exists with story entries and issues.yaml exists with issue entries\n36\t   **When** `loadWorkItems()` is called\n37\t   **Then** it returns a combined, ordered list of work items (stories and issues) ready for execution\n38\t   **And** issues are included alongside stories — the engine does not distinguish between them\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t6. **Given** no `issues.yaml` file exists at the expected path\n42\t   **When** `loadWorkItems()` is called\n43\t   **Then** it returns only stories from sprint-status.yaml without error\n44\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n45\t\n46\t7. **Given** a `per-run` task (e.g., `verify`)\n47\t   **When** the engine processes it in the flow\n48\t   **Then** it dispatches the agent exactly once (not once per story)\n49\t   **And** records a single `TaskCheckpoint` with `story_key: \"__run__\"` or similar sentinel\n50\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n51\t\n52\t8. **Given** the engine encounters a `loop:` block in the flow array\n53\t   **When** it processes the flow step\n54\t   **Then** it skips the loop block without error (loop execution is story 5-2)\n55\t   **And** logs a warning that loop blocks are not yet implemented\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t9. **Given** a task with `source_access: false`\n59\t   **When** the engine dispatches it\n60\t   **Then** it calls `createIsolatedWorkspace()` before dispatch and `cleanup()` after\n61\t   **And** passes the workspace's `toDispatchOptions()` to `dispatchAgent()`\n62\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n63\t\n64\t10. **Given** a task with `source_access: true` (default)\n65\t    **When** the engine dispatches it\n66\t    **Then** it dispatches with `cwd: process.cwd()` (the project directory)\n67\t    **And** does NOT create an isolated workspace\n68\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n69\t\n70\t11. **Given** the engine starts a workflow execution\n71\t    **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called\n72\t    **Then** it generates a trace ID via `generateTraceId()` for each task dispatch\n73\t    **And** injects the trace prompt via `formatTracePrompt()` into `DispatchOptions.appendSystemPrompt`\n74\t    **And** records the trace ID in workflow state via `recordTraceId()`\n75\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n76\t\n77\t12. **Given** a task with `session: continue`\n78\t    **When** the engine dispatches it\n79\t    **Then** it calls `resolveSessionId('continue', ...)` to look up the previous session ID\n80\t    **And** passes the result as `DispatchOptions.sessionId`\n81\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n82\t\n83\t13. **Given** `dispatchAgent()` throws a `DispatchError`\n84\t    **When** the engine catches it\n85\t    **Then** it records the failure in workflow state (phase set to `\"error\"`, task checkpoint with error info)\n86\t    **And** writes state to disk\n87\t    **And** re-throws or returns an `EngineResult` with `success: false` and the error details\n88\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n89\t\n90\t14. **Given** unit tests for the workflow engine module\n91\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n92\t    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for `workflow-engine.ts` covering: sequential execution, per-story dispatch, per-run dispatch, state checkpointing, work item loading, source isolation integration, trace ID injection, session boundary resolution, error handling, and loop block skipping\n93\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n94\t\n95\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n96\t\n97\t- [x] Task 1: Define engine interfaces and types (AC: #1)\n98\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`\n99\t  - [x] Define `EngineConfig` interface: `{ workflow: ResolvedWorkflow; agents: Record<string, SubagentDefinition>; sprintStatusPath: string; issuesPath?: string; runId: string; projectDir?: string }`\n100\t  - [x] Define `EngineResult` interface: `{ success: boolean; tasksCompleted: number; storiesProcessed: number; errors: EngineError[]; durationMs: number }`\n101\t  - [x] Define `EngineError` interface: `{ taskName: string; storyKey: string; code: string; message: string }`\n102\t  - [x] Define `WorkItem` interface: `{ key: string; title?: string; source: 'sprint' | 'issues' }`\n103\t\n104\t- [x] Task 2: Implement work item loading (AC: #5, #6)\n105\t  - [x] Implement `loadWorkItems(sprintStatusPath: string, issuesPath?: string): WorkItem[]`\n106\t  - [x] Parse sprint-status.yaml `development_status` section — extract story keys with status `backlog` or `ready-for-dev`\n107\t  - [x] Parse issues.yaml if it exists — extract issue entries with status `backlog` or `ready-for-dev`\n108\t  - [x] If issues.yaml missing, return stories only (no error)\n109\t  - [x] Return combined list: stories first, then issues (simple ordering for now)\n110\t\n111\t- [x] Task 3: Implement single task dispatch (AC: #4, #9, #10, #11, #12)\n112\t  - [x] Implement `dispatchTask(task: ResolvedTask, taskName: string, storyKey: string, definition: SubagentDefinition, state: WorkflowState, config: EngineConfig): Promise<WorkflowState>`\n113\t  - [x] If `task.source_access === false`: create isolated workspace, get dispatch options, dispatch, cleanup\n114\t  - [x] If `task.source_access === true`: dispatch with `cwd: config.projectDir ?? process.cwd()`\n115\t  - [x] Generate trace ID with `generateTraceId(config.runId, state.iteration, taskName)`\n116\t  - [x] Inject trace prompt via `formatTracePrompt()` into `appendSystemPrompt`\n117\t  - [x] Resolve session ID via `resolveSessionId(task.session, ...)`\n118\t  - [x] After dispatch: record session ID, record trace ID, append TaskCheckpoint, write state\n119\t\n120\t- [x] Task 4: Implement flow execution loop (AC: #2, #3, #7, #8)\n121\t  - [x] Implement main `executeWorkflow(config: EngineConfig): Promise<EngineResult>` function\n122\t  - [x] Read or initialize workflow state; set `phase: \"executing\"`, `started`, `workflow_name`\n123\t  - [x] Load work items via `loadWorkItems()`\n124\t  - [x] Iterate through `config.workflow.flow` steps:\n125\t    - If step is a `string` (task name): look up task in `config.workflow.tasks`\n126\t      - If `scope: per-story`: dispatch once per work item\n127\t      - If `scope: per-run`: dispatch once with sentinel story key `\"__run__\"`\n128\t    - If step is a `LoopBlock`: log warning, skip (story 5-2)\n129\t  - [x] After all flow steps: set `phase: \"completed\"`, write final state\n130\t  - [x] Return `EngineResult`\n131\t\n132\t- [x] Task 5: Implement error handling (AC: #13)\n133\t  - [x] Wrap `dispatchAgent()` calls in try/catch\n134\t  - [x] On `DispatchError`: record error in state, set `phase: \"error\"`, write state, collect error in result\n135\t  - [x] Continue to next story/task or halt based on error severity (RATE_LIMIT → halt, NETWORK → halt, SDK_INIT → halt, UNKNOWN → record and continue)\n136\t\n137\t- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #14)\n138\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n139\t  - [x] Mock `dispatchAgent()` from `agent-dispatch.ts` — return fake `DispatchResult`\n140\t  - [x] Mock `writeWorkflowState()` and `readWorkflowState()` from `workflow-state.ts`\n141\t  - [x] Mock `createIsolatedWorkspace()` from `source-isolation.ts`\n142\t  - [x] Mock `generateTraceId()`, `formatTracePrompt()`, `recordTraceId()` from `trace-id.ts`\n143\t  - [x] Mock `resolveSessionId()`, `recordSessionId()` from `session-manager.ts`\n144\t  - [x] Test: sequential flow steps execute in order\n145\t  - [x] Test: per-story task dispatches once per story\n146\t  - [x] Test: per-run task dispatches exactly once\n147\t  - [x] Test: state written after each task completion\n148\t  - [x] Test: source isolation invoked for `source_access: false`\n149\t  - [x] Test: source isolation NOT invoked for `source_access: true`\n150\t  - [x] Test: trace ID generated and injected per dispatch\n151\t  - [x] Test: session boundary resolved per dispatch\n152\t  - [x] Test: DispatchError caught and recorded\n153\t  - [x] Test: loop blocks skipped with warning\n154\t  - [x] Test: work items loaded from sprint-status only when no issues.yaml\n155\t  - [x] Test: work items loaded from both sprint-status and issues.yaml\n156\t  - [x] Verify 80%+ coverage on `workflow-engine.ts`\n157\t\n158\t## Dev Notes\n159\t\n160\t### Module Design\n161\t\n162\t`workflow-engine.ts` is the orchestrator module — it imports and composes all other modules built in epics 1-4. It does NOT implement loop iteration logic (story 5-2), crash recovery/resume (story 5-3), or CLI commands (story 5-4). This story creates the core sequential execution path only.\n163\t\n164\t### Integration Points\n165\t\n166\tThe engine connects these existing modules:\n167\t- `workflow-parser.ts` — provides `ResolvedWorkflow` with tasks and flow (input to engine, resolved externally)\n168\t- `agent-resolver.ts` — provides `SubagentDefinition` (compiled agents, resolved externally and passed in via `EngineConfig.agents`)\n169\t- `agent-dispatch.ts` — `dispatchAgent()` for SDK session execution\n170\t- `workflow-state.ts` — `readWorkflowState()`, `writeWorkflowState()` for crash-safe checkpointing\n171\t- `source-isolation.ts` — `createIsolatedWorkspace()` for `source_access: false` tasks\n172\t- `trace-id.ts` — `generateTraceId()`, `formatTracePrompt()`, `recordTraceId()`\n173\t- `session-manager.ts` — `resolveSessionId()`, `recordSessionId()`\n174\t\n175\t### Data Flow\n176\t\n177\t```\n178\texecuteWorkflow(config)\n179\t  1. readWorkflowState() — load existing state or create default\n180\t  2. loadWorkItems(sprintStatusPath, issuesPath) — get stories + issues\n181\t  3. For each flow step:\n182\t     a. If string task name:\n183\t        - per-story: for each work item → dispatchTask()\n184\t        - per-run: dispatchTask() once with sentinel key\n185\t     b. If LoopBlock: skip (story 5-2)\n186\t  4. writeWorkflowState() — final state\n187\t  5. Return EngineResult\n188\t```\n189\t\n190\t### dispatchTask() Flow\n191\t\n192\t```\n193\tdispatchTask(task, taskName, storyKey, definition, state, config)\n194\t  1. generateTraceId() → traceId\n195\t  2. formatTracePrompt(traceId) → tracePrompt\n196\t  3. resolveSessionId(task.session, { taskName, storyKey }, state) → sessionId\n197\t  4. If source_access === false:\n198\t       createIsolatedWorkspace({ runId, storyFiles: [...] })\n199\t       dispatchOptions = workspace.toDispatchOptions()\n200\t     Else:\n201\t       dispatchOptions = { cwd: projectDir }\n202\t  5. dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, { ...dispatchOptions, sessionId, appendSystemPrompt: tracePrompt })\n203\t  6. recordSessionId({ taskName, storyKey }, result.sessionId, state)\n204\t  7. recordTraceId(traceId, state)\n205\t  8. Append TaskCheckpoint to state\n206\t  9. writeWorkflowState(state)\n207\t  10. If source_access === false: workspace.cleanup()\n208\t```\n209\t\n210\t### Sprint-Status Parsing\n211\t\n212\tThe engine reads `sprint-status.yaml` to find work items. Format:\n213\t```yaml\n214\tdevelopment_status:\n215\t  epic-5: backlog\n216\t  5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps: backlog\n217\t  5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks: backlog\n218\t```\n219\t\n220\tParsing rules:\n221\t- Skip keys matching `epic-*` (epic groupings, not stories)\n222\t- Skip keys ending in `-retrospective`\n223\t- Include entries with status `backlog` or `ready-for-dev`\n224\t- Story key format: `{epic_num}-{story_num}-{slug}`\n225\t\n226\t### Issues.yaml Format\n227\t\n228\tPer AD6 in architecture-v2.md:\n229\t```yaml\n230\tissues:\n231\t  - id: issue-001\n232\t    title: Docker timeout handling too aggressive\n233\t    source: retro-epic-15\n234\t    priority: high\n235\t    status: ready-for-dev\n236\t```\n237\t\n238\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n239\t\n240\t- Does NOT implement `loop:` block execution — that's story 5-2\n241\t- Does NOT implement crash recovery / resume from checkpoint — that's story 5-3\n242\t- Does NOT implement the `codeharness run` CLI command — that's story 5-4\n243\t- Does NOT implement evaluator logic — that's Epic 6\n244\t- Does NOT implement circuit breaker — that's Epic 7\n245\t- Does NOT implement finding injection into retry prompts — that's story 5-2\n246\t- Does NOT parse workflow YAML — `ResolvedWorkflow` is passed in via config\n247\t- Does NOT resolve agents — `SubagentDefinition` map is passed in via config\n248\t\n249\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n250\t\n251\t- **Do NOT import `parseWorkflow`** — the engine receives an already-resolved workflow\n252\t- **Do NOT import `resolveAgent` or `compileSubagentDefinition`** — agents are pre-compiled and passed in\n253\t- **Do NOT implement retry/loop logic** — skip `LoopBlock` flow steps with a log\n254\t- **Do NOT cache state in memory across task boundaries** — always write to disk after each task (crash recovery guarantee)\n255\t- **Do NOT use `child_process.spawn`** — agent dispatch is via `dispatchAgent()` only\n256\t- **Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml** — the engine reads it but never writes to it (story status updates are a separate concern)\n257\t\n258\t### Prompt Construction for Tasks\n259\t\n260\tThe engine must construct a prompt for each dispatch. For per-story tasks, the prompt should include:\n261\t- The story key and any available story context\n262\t- The task's `prompt_template` if defined (future: template rendering)\n263\t- For now, a simple prompt with the story key: `\"Implement story {storyKey}\"`\n264\t\n265\tFor per-run tasks, the prompt should reference the overall run context.\n266\t\n267\t### Project Structure Notes\n268\t\n269\t- New file: `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — core execution orchestrator\n270\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n271\t- No modified files — this module is additive only\n272\t- Aligns with architecture: each module in `src/lib/` is one file with co-located test\n273\t\n274\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n275\t\n276\tFrom story 4-4 (source isolation):\n277\t- Source isolation is a standalone module, not part of agent-dispatch — the engine calls it directly\n278\t- `createIsolatedWorkspace()` takes `{ runId, storyFiles }`, returns `IsolatedWorkspace` with `toDispatchOptions()` and `cleanup()`\n279\t- Missing story files are warned and skipped, not thrown\n280\t- Cleanup is idempotent\n281\t\n282\tFrom story 4-3 (trace IDs):\n283\t- `generateTraceId(runId, iteration, taskName)` — format: `ch-{runId}-{iteration}-{taskName}`\n284\t- `formatTracePrompt(traceId)` — returns string for `appendSystemPrompt`\n285\t- `recordTraceId(traceId, state)` — returns new state (immutable)\n286\t\n287\tFrom story 4-2 (session boundaries):\n288\t- `resolveSessionId(boundary, key, state)` — returns session ID or undefined\n289\t- `recordSessionId(key, sessionId, state)` — returns new state with checkpoint (immutable)\n290\t\n291\tFrom story 4-1 (agent dispatch):\n292\t- `dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, options?)` — returns `Promise<DispatchResult>`\n293\t- `DispatchResult` has `{ sessionId, success, durationMs, output }`\n294\t- `DispatchError` has `{ code, agentName, cause }` — codes: RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, SDK_INIT, UNKNOWN\n295\t\n296\t### Testing Strategy\n297\t\n298\tHeavy mocking approach — the engine is an orchestrator, so tests verify correct composition of the underlying modules. All dependencies (`dispatchAgent`, `writeWorkflowState`, `createIsolatedWorkspace`, `generateTraceId`, etc.) are mocked via `vi.mock()`. Tests verify:\n299\t1. Correct call sequences (e.g., state written after dispatch, not before)\n300\t2. Correct arguments passed to each dependency\n301\t3. Error handling paths\n302\t4. Per-story vs per-run dispatch semantics\n303\t\n304\t### References\n305\t\n306\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 5.1: Flow Execution — Sequential Steps]\n307\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — workflow-engine]\n308\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Integration Boundaries & Data Flow]\n309\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — ResolvedWorkflow, ResolvedTask, FlowStep, LoopBlock]\n310\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts — dispatchAgent(), DispatchResult, DispatchError, DispatchOptions]\n311\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — WorkflowState, TaskCheckpoint, readWorkflowState(), writeWorkflowState()]\n312\t- [Source: src/lib/source-isolation.ts — createIsolatedWorkspace(), IsolatedWorkspace, IsolationOptions]\n313\t- [Source: src/lib/trace-id.ts — generateTraceId(), formatTracePrompt(), recordTraceId()]\n314\t- [Source: src/lib/session-manager.ts — resolveSessionId(), recordSessionId(), SessionBoundary]\n315\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — SubagentDefinition]\n316\t- [Source: templates/workflows/default.yaml — default flow: implement → verify → loop]\n317\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-4-source-isolation-enforcement.md — predecessor story]\n318\t\n319\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n320\t## Verification Requirements\n321\t\n322\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps-proof.md)\n323\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n324\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n325\t\n326\t## Documentation Requirements\n327\t\n328\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n329\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps.md\n330\t\n331\t## Testing Requirements\n332\t\n333\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n334\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n335\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n336\t\n337\t## Dev Agent Record\n338\t\n339\t### Agent Model Used\n340\t\n341\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n342\t\n343\t### Debug Log References\n344\t\n345\tN/A\n346\t\n347\t### Completion Notes List\n348\t\n349\t- Implemented `workflow-engine.ts` as the core orchestrator module composing all Epic 1-4 modules\n350\t- Exports: `executeWorkflow()`, `dispatchTask()`, `loadWorkItems()`, plus interfaces `EngineConfig`, `EngineResult`, `EngineError`, `WorkItem`\n351\t- `loadWorkItems()` parses sprint-status.yaml and optionally issues.yaml, filtering for backlog/ready-for-dev items, excluding epics and retrospectives\n352\t- `dispatchTask()` handles trace ID generation/injection, session resolution, source isolation (for source_access: false), agent dispatch, state checkpointing, and cleanup\n353\t- `executeWorkflow()` orchestrates sequential flow execution: per-story tasks dispatch once per work item, per-run tasks dispatch once with `__run__` sentinel\n354\t- Loop blocks skipped with warning (deferred to story 5-2)\n355\t- Error handling: RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors halt execution; UNKNOWN errors record and continue\n356\t- 31 unit tests covering all acceptance criteria, 89.91% statement coverage, 100% function coverage\n357\t- All 3955 tests pass with zero regressions\n358\t\n359\t### Change Log\n360\t\n361\t- 2026-04-03: Story 5-1 implemented — workflow engine sequential execution\n362\t\n363\t### File List\n364\t\n365\t- src/lib/workflow-engine.ts (new)\n366\t- src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts (new)\n367\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011dV6c9xFAQaHP6KDdoVM36","session_id":"7bb08296-a865-42eb-9710-ebdb6ccedbda","uuid":"137ce126-acf9-42e4-b3bc-f21db69d4feb","timestamp":"2026-04-02T21:54:22.472Z"}
