{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011dV6c9xFAQaHP6KDdoVM36","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps\n**Files reviewed:** `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`, `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n**Tests:** 39 passed (was 31), 3963 total suite passes, 0 regressions\n**Coverage:** 99.2% stmt / 87.01% branch / 100% func / 100% line (was 89.91% / 81.33% / 100% / 90.59%)\n**Overall coverage:** 96.76%, all 158 files above 80% floor\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n**HIGH:**\n1. **RATE_LIMIT halt only exits inner loop, not outer flow loop** -- Per-story tasks encountering RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors would `break` the inner `for (item of workItems)` loop but continue to the next flow step. Fixed with a `halted` flag that breaks the outer flow loop too.\n\n2. **No TaskCheckpoint recorded on dispatch failure (AC #13 violation)** -- AC #13 requires \"task checkpoint with error info\" on failure. The code only set `phase: 'error'` without appending a checkpoint. Added `recordErrorInState()` helper that appends a TaskCheckpoint with task_name, story_key, and completed_at.\n\n**MEDIUM:**\n3. **Coverage gaps** -- Added 8 new tests covering: unreadable sprint-status.yaml, unreadable issues.yaml, invalid issues.yaml YAML, missing task definition skip, no-sessionId dispatch path, RATE_LIMIT halt across flow steps, error checkpoint recording, non-Error exception handling.\n\n4. **Dead variable** -- Removed unused `callCount` variable in test.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop -- only the inner work-items loop. The engine would proceed to the next flow step (e.g., `verify`) after a rate limit during `implement`. Fixed.\n- HIGH: Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- The `else` branch in `dispatchTask` (lines 246-255) for missing `result.sessionId` duplicates checkpoint creation logic that `recordSessionId` also does. Could be refactored to a single path.\n- `handleDispatchError` and `recordErrorInState` are separate functions that could be merged or chained more cleanly.\n- The `warn()` calls for skipped tasks/agents don't propagate to `EngineResult.errors`, making silent skip failures invisible to the caller.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch coverage at 87% -- remaining uncovered branches are defensive null/type checks on YAML parse results (`parsed && typeof parsed === 'object'`) that can't be easily triggered when `yaml.parse` is fully mocked.\n- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML is mocked).\n- No test for `projectDir` defaulting to `process.cwd()` when omitted from config.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None significant. The orchestrator pattern is clean -- it composes modules without importing parse/resolve logic.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 5, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~10 lines visible), `npx vitest run --coverage` initial run (~80 lines, truncated), `git diff --name-only` (~11 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: Ran coverage grep 3 times with different patterns before finding the right one. The first `--coverage` run output was truncated and required re-runs."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a26e9bcdbd061c4a4 (use SendMessage with to: 'a26e9bcdbd061c4a4' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63593\ntool_uses: 42\nduration_ms: 270617</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bb08296-a865-42eb-9710-ebdb6ccedbda","uuid":"85b79249-139c-4676-8cf4-43b349010690","timestamp":"2026-04-