{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GDsJxA49uDa2Cnnd8mgnYn","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bb08296-a865-42eb-9710-ebdb6ccedbda","uuid":"42c74a5f-f5fb-42d7-a057-5c41e46799d8","timestamp":"2026-04-02T22:03:08.305Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none","newString":"- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps — code-review (2026-04-03T01:55)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop — only the inner work-items loop. Fixed.\n- HIGH: Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Coverage gaps — added 8 new tests. Coverage now 99.2% stmt / 87% branch.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):**\n- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in dispatchTask else branch\n- handleDispatchError and recordErrorInState could be merged\n- warn() calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to EngineResult.errors\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch coverage at 87% — remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results\n- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 5, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~80 lines), vitest full suite (~10 lines), git diff --name-only (~11 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Ran coverage grep 3 times with different patterns","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — create-story (2026-04-03T00:25)\n\n- **Risk: `trace_ids` field on WorkflowState** — adding optional field requires updating `isValidWorkflowState()`. Made optional to avoid breaking existing states.\n- All 9 ACs are test-provable. Pure logic module with no I/O.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Glob: 3\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — dev-story (2026-04-03T00:30)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Write: 2, Bash: 4, Glob: 1\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — code-review (2026-04-03T00:37)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `generateTraceId` accepted NaN/Infinity/negative/float iteration values. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: No segment length cap — unbounded trace IDs. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `formatTracePrompt('')` silently produced empty trace marker. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `workflow-state.ts` coverage at 79.06%, below 80% floor. Fixed with 10 new tests.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):** duplicate trace ID guard missing; empty runId+taskName produces ugly ID; sanitizeSegment strips non-ASCII.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 7, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n\n### 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection — verification (2026-04-03T00:55)\n\n- **`npx codeharness verify` fails** due to stale `AGENTS.md` — wants documentation for new modules in `src/lib/` (agent-dispatch.ts, agent-resolver.ts, session-manager.ts, trace-id.ts). Documentation debt, not a story 4-3 issue.\n- Build, tests (36/36), and coverage (100% trace-id.ts) all clean.\n- All 9 ACs verified with evidence.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: test:unit run (~50 lines), trace-id verbose test (~40 lines), coverage (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: codeharness verify called twice\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — create-story (2026-04-03T01:05)\n\n- **Risk:** AC #4 depends on `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` having `disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]` from story 3-2. Not verified that template exists.\n- `/tmp/` path pattern is Unix-specific. Not a concern on darwin but noted for portability.\n- All 9 ACs are test-provable (pure file system operations testable with real temp dirs).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Read: 7, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (architecture-v2.md: 2 reads)\n- Redundant operations: Two Grep calls to `source_access` could have been one\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — dev-story (2026-04-03T01:10)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 15\n- By tool: Read: 5, Bash: 4, Grep: 4, Write: 2, Edit: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~160 lines), full test suite (~20 lines), tsc noEmit (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — code-review (2026-04-03T01:18)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Path traversal via runId injection — unsanitized user input in file path. Fixed with `sanitizeRunId()`.\n- HIGH: Silent file overwrite on basename collision — data loss. Fixed with `deduplicateFilename()`.\n- MEDIUM: Stale workspace contamination from crashed runs. Fixed with pre-creation cleanup.\n- MEDIUM: Missing edge case tests for sanitization, dedup, return shape. Fixed.\n\n**LOW (not fixed):** deduplicateFilename counter loop unbounded; hardcoded `/tmp/` base path.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage (~80 lines), git status (~30 lines), git diff (~16 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: minor — two test assertion corrections needed\n\n### 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement — verification (2026-04-03T01:30)\n\n- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure:** The verify command checks global harness state (`tests_passed`, `coverage_met` flags) which are not set by manual test runs. Harness-level tracking issue, not a story defect.\n- **AGENTS.md stale:** verify command flagged `src/lib/AGENTS.md` as missing entry for `source-isolation.ts`. Documentation gap, not an AC requirement.\n- Build, tests (21 source-isolation tests, 3924 total), and coverage (100% source-isolation.ts) all clean.\n- All 9 ACs verified with evidence.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: test:unit (~50 lines), coverage full run (~40 lines), evaluator.yaml (~22 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Coverage run twice (once default, once targeted)\n\n### 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps — create-story (2026-04-03T01:37)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** issues.yaml schema (FR40-41) is only sketched in AD6 — exact key format assumed without validation.\n- **Prompt construction underspecified:** minimal prompt approach used, likely needs refinement later.\n- **Loop block deferral:** AC #8 defers loop blocks to story 5-2 with skip+warn.\n- All 14 ACs are test-provable (pure orchestrator, all behavior verifiable with mocked deps).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 12, Glob: 5, Grep: 1, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps — dev-story (2026-04-03T01:48)\n\n- **Boundary test enforcement:** Project convention requires `// IGNORE:` comments on all catch blocks. Missed on first pass, fixed after test failure.\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 pre-existing TS errors unrelated to this story. Not fixed.\n- **Coverage gaps:** Lines 148-152 (null check on parsed issues YAML) and lines 316-317, 405 (edge cases in flow execution) uncovered. Defensive null checks hard to trigger through mock setup. Coverage still at 89.91%.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 13, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~30 lines), full test suite (~20 lines), type check (~2 lines)\n- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":123,"oldLines":3,"newStart":123,"newLines":26,"lines":[" - Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~30 lines), full test suite (~20 lines), type check (~2 lines)"," - Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads"," - Redundant operations: none","+","+### 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps — code-review (2026-04-03T01:55)","+","+**Bugs found:**","+- HIGH: Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop — only the inner work-items loop. Fixed.","+- HIGH: Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Fixed.","+- MEDIUM: Coverage gaps — added 8 new tests. Coverage now 99.2% stmt / 87% branch.","+","+**LOW (not fixed):**","+- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in dispatchTask else branch","+- handleDispatchError and recordErrorInState could be merged","+- warn() calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to EngineResult.errors","+","+**Coverage gaps:**","+- Branch coverage at 87% — remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results","+- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: 23","+- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 5, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 2, Skill: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~80 lines), vitest full suite (~10 lines), git diff --name-only (~11 lines)","+- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads","+- Redundant operations: Ran coverage grep 3 times with different patterns"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
